properties.headline: Winter Weather Advisory issued January 26 at 1:21PM CST until January 27 at 6:00AM CST by NWS Twin Cities/Chanhassen MN
properties.description:
...FREEZING DRIZZLE WITH LIGHT ICE ACCUMULATIONS POSSIBLE FROM
WEST CENTRAL INTO SOUTHWEST MINNESOTA TONIGHT...

.Freezing drizzle is expected to develop over west central and
southwest Minnesota tonight, and remain possible into the early
morning hours on Monday. A light glazing of ice is possible,
especially on untreated roads, bridges and sidewalks.

* WHAT...Freezing drizzle expected. Total ice accumulations of a
light glaze.

* WHERE...Stevens, Lac Qui Parle, Swift, Chippewa and Yellow
Medicine Counties.

* WHEN...From 6 PM this evening to 6 AM CST Monday.

* IMPACTS...Very slippery sidewalks, roads and bridges are
possible.
properties.instruction:
Slow down and use caution while traveling. Prepare for possible
power outages.

The latest road conditions for the state you are calling from can
be obtained by calling 5 1 1.

NWSheadline: WINTER WEATHER ADVISORY IN EFFECT FROM 6 PM THIS EVENING TO 6 AM CST MONDAY
